{
  "answer": "**The matla (opening couplet) of chapter 200 (\"Woh meri cheen-e-jabeen se gham-e-pinhan samjha\") in Mirza Ghalib's *Diwan-E-Ghalib* is:**\n\n> Woh meri cheen-e-jabeen se gham-e-pinhan samjha  \n> Raaz-e-maktoob ba-be-rabti-e-unwan samjha[^1]\n\n**English translation:**\n\n> My brow's deep lines revealed my secret, hidden pain, I thought.  \n> A tangled title made the letter's meaning plain, I thought.[^2]\n\nThis is the first *sher* (couplet) of the ghazal, as is standard for the *matlaʿ* in Urdu ghazal poetry.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/200-woh-meri-cheen-e-jabeen-se-gham-e-pinhan-samjha/transliteration/#p-966218).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/200-woh-meri-cheen-e-jabeen-se-gham-e-pinhan-samjha/translation/#p-3be334).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [chapter](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/200-woh-meri-cheen-e-jabeen-se-gham-e-pinhan-samjha/translation/).",
